Thinly slice the @mushrooms{150%grams}.

Trim the @pak choi{1%unit}, then separate the leaves.

Pick the @coriander{5%grams}(leaves picked) leaves from their stalks.

Place a large #pot{} over a medium heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @sesame seeds{1%sachet} and dry-fry, stirring regularly, until
lightly toasted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once toasted remove from the pot and set aside for serving.

> TIP: Watch them like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Return the (now empty) pot to a high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, add the mushrooms. Fry until browned, stirring occasionally,
~{4-5%minutes}.

Add the pak choi and another drizzle of oil if necessary.

Cook for ~{3-4%minutes} until wilted, shifting occasionally.

Add the @Thai style spice mix{1%sachet} and cook for ~{30%seconds} until
aromatic, shifting frequently.

Add the @harissa paste{1%sachet}, @vegetable stock{1%sachet}, @soy sauce{2%sachets},
@honey{1%sachet} and @water{600%ml}.

> Double water for 4p.

Bring to the boil then simmer for ~{7-8%minutes}.

Add the @udon noodles{300%grams} to the stock and cook until warmed through,
~{1-2%minutes}.

Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

== Soft-Boiled Egg ==

While the broth simmers, bring a separate #pot{} of water to the boil over a
medium-high heat.

Once boiling, carefully add your @?egg{1%per person} to the water.

Simmer gently for ~eggs{4-6%minutes} for a soft-boiled egg.

Once cooked to your preference, transfer from the pot to a #bowl{} of cold water
—this will stop it cooking any further!

Carefully peel the egg then halve lengthways.

== To Serve ==

Divide your spicy ramen between #bowls{}.

Top with the optional egg.

Scatter over the sesame seeds and picked coriander leaves.